					<article id="post-595" class="post-595 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized clearfix" role="article">
						
						<header>
						
							<a href="http://techblog.hybris.com/2014/03/26/internet-of-things-an-overview/" title="Internet of Things &#8211; an overview"></a>
							
							<div class="page-header"><h1 class="h2"><a href="http://techblog.hybris.com/2014/03/26/internet-of-things-an-overview/" rel="bookmark" title="Internet of Things &#8211; an overview">Internet of Things &#8211; an overview</a></h1></div>
							
							<p class="meta">Posted <time datetime="2014-03-26" pubdate>March 26, 2014</time> by <a href="<a href="http://techblog.hybris.com/author/hansamann/" title="Posts by hansamann" rel="author">hansamann</a><span class="amp"> -</span> filed under <a href="http://techblog.hybris.com/category/uncategorized/" title="View all posts in Uncategorized" rel="category tag">Uncategorized</a>.</p>
						
						</header> <!-- end article header -->
					
						<section class="post_content clearfix">
							<p>This is a presentation I gave at the Mobile Tech Conference last week &#8211; it was very well attended, the topic seems to be getting more and more attention. From labs, we&#8217;re working on a few IoT applications in the retail and commerce space, too early to talk and write about, but the presentation is really an effort to bring to together all our findings and learnings so far. <a href="https://plus.google.com/communities/109078776849083294736">Happy to discuss in the hybris G+ Group. </a></p>
<p><iframe src="http://prezi.com/embed/-35jarymj-4t/?bgcolor=ffffff&amp;lock_to_path=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;autohide_ctrls=0&amp;features=undefined&amp;disabled_features=undefined" width="550" height="400" frameBorder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozAllowFullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
						</section> <!-- end article section -->
						
						<section class="mini-comments">
							<a href="http://techblog.hybris.com/2014/03/26/internet-of-things-an-overview/#respond" title="Comment on Internet of Things &#8211; an overview">Be the first to comment this post</a>						</section>
						
